President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Richard Giacolone of Virginia to be the Director of the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service. Giacolone currently serves as the Deputy Director of FMCS and has held this position since June 2018. He has a long career at FMCS, including directing the International/Administrative Dispute Resolution Department and serving as a special assistant to the director. Prior to his work at FMCS, Giacolone was a commissioner in the Chesapeake, Virginia field office. He also worked as a Labor Relations Advisor for the Department of the Navy and received the Meritorious Civilian Service Medal for his contributions to the Department of Navy Labor and Employee Relations program. Giacolone holds a Bachelor of Science degree in industrial psychology and a Master of Public Administration degree from Old Dominion University.